immediately rushed to hospital for medical attention.Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said it is
alleged that the victim left his home to Groblersdal town, together with his
wife for shopping.Ngoepe said on arrival, the wife went to another shop
leaving him queuing inside the ABSA bank to get money.She waited for the husband until she realised that he was
not coming back and she decided to go outside to the parking lot  to check him. On arrival, she was
surprised to find the car had moved  from
where it was parked and at a later stage, she saw it driving away very fast
within the CBD. Ngeope said, she tried to call the husband repeatedly until
his cell phone was answered by an unknown man who later dropped that call, the
Police were notified and a search operation ensued.He was driving a white Isuzu double cab.Ngoepe said the suspects involved in this matter are still
unknown and there are no arrest made yet.